<Author>rklarer99
<Content>A nice stay! I have stayed at Candlewood Suites before -- this same one, for example -- and, as usual, had a good stay. The General Manager is up front and hands on to keep the place in good condition -- and he even helped on the front desk to do our check-in. It was a good experience right from the start!The Candlewood Cupboard was helpful as we needed a few supplies - including soap to do the dirty laundry that was piling up from the first part of our roadtrip (FREE use of machines, I might add!).Also, this is the first and only Candlewood that I've ever seen with a pool -- but it is a GREAT amenity! The pool and area was very well maintained and was definitely enjoyed after driving so many hours and being in the middle of the recent heat wave.The room is a typical Candlewood suite...but it's GREAT to know what you're going to get! The surprise on this was we were put into a one-bedroom suite -- at the same price as a regular suite! The extra room made it more like home.There is a Texas Land and Cattle restaurant within a short drive from the hotel. GREAT food! GREAT service! I want to go back to Texas just to get more ribs and then go swim in the hotel pool!The check-out process was also just as efficient and we were on our way to our next stop in no time.Once again, great work, Candlewood! 
