<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Candlewood Rocks!!!! My husband and I spent our week vacation there with our 4 year old and it was GREAT. We had the one bedroom suite which gave us ample room with a kitchen (and 2 TV's, very important that Baylee not miss her beloved cartoons!!) It had high speed internet access for me and was just minutes away from the Mav's at the American Airlines Center for my husband. It sits right on Stemmons so you have easy access to anywhere you want to go only about 20 minutes or so from Six Flags (without 5:00 traffic of course) The pool is enclosed in the middle so the public can't get to it. They had a reception one night with BBQ for all the guest. I left a note for the mgr about DSL at the pool area and he was quick to respond to me with a solution for the next time we stay there. The staff is very helpful anytime you need something. They have on-site groceries you can purchase(on the honor system no less) a library with books to take to your room, large TV, electric massage chair, and fresh bagels in the am. What more could you want? The longer you stay the better deal you get on the rates. (that was my experience while planning the trip anyway) 2 thumbs up!! Laurie B. Anson, Tx 
